speakers:


### Shivam Singhal

Shivam is an open source developer. He has experience working remotely with open source projects like Mozilla Firefox, CNCF, Linux foundation and building communities. He loves to mentor folks get started with open source. He writes blogs at https://itsopensource.com/, maintains Documentation of Firefox https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/. He also loves to travel, teach, and speak about open source and advocates for Diversity in Tech.

---
abstract:

Documentation is critical in creating a successful open source project. As open source maintainers we struggle to have a great documentation because of time and skills but great documentation and community support are keys for project success.
---
full_description:

As open source maintainers we struggle to have a great documentation because of time and skills but great documentation and community support are keys for project success. 

In this talk I will go how to think about documentation from a user or a contributor perspective We will go over topics like - How do you organize your docs?  What sections do you need? How much detail should you add? What baseline knowledge can you assume your audience has?
